	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />In a couple weeks I'm going to be working on a simple cart hack, as my first NES project. If I put in a ZIF socket, I'm going to need to cut the cart. I've seen some nice scans of devcarts with ZIF sockets, and some nasty ones.
<br />
<br />Any hints on cutting the plastic so it doesn't look like it was chewed out by a large rat?
<br />
<br />NC

		

		</td>
