	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />Are you sure about ZIF sockets?  They're always bigger than the chips, and the ones I've seen have huge leads too.  So they'd have trouble fitting, in various ways.  Unless you know of a certain kind that'd work well?
<br />
<br />My solution was to install a plain IC socket on the board, and put my chips in sockets also.  So the contact is only socket-to-socket.  Makes it really easy to remove, and no problems with bent pins.  Of course then the chips are kinda.. elevated off the board.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


